A man was arrested and charged in Prince William County in connection with his relationship with a girl he met on the social media platform , the county police said. They said the man and a 12-year-old girl met on “Instagram.” He went to her house in King George County, Va., on Monday, and brought her to Prince William. County police said Tyquan Bernard Stoney, 20, of Belvedere Drive in the Woodbridge area was arrested Tuesday and charged with two counts of rape. 